  "prompt": "Is it the norm to put your degrees in your email signature?",
  "response": "Including your degrees in your email signature can vary depending on the context and industry. In some professional fields, such as academia, healthcare, law, or engineering, it is quite common and often expected to include your degrees and professional titles in your email signature. This helps establish credibility and authority in communications.\n\nIn other industries, it may be less common, and the decision to include your degrees can depend on personal preference, company culture, and the nature of your interactions. If you are unsure, you might consider observing the email signature practices of colleagues or industry peers, or asking for guidance from your organization's HR or communications department.\n\nUltimately, if you choose to include your degrees in your email signature, ensure that it remains professional, concise, and relevant to the context of your communications.",
